In mathematics, '''Denisyuk polynomials''' De<sub>''n''</sub>(''x'') or ''M''<sub>''n''</sub>(''x'') are generalizations of the [[Laguerre polynomials]] introduced by {{harvtxt|Denisyuk|1954}} given by the [[generating function]]

:<math>\displaystyle \sum_{n=0}^\infty t^nM_n(x)=\frac 1{1+t}\exp-\frac{xt}{1-t}

</math>
{{harv|Boas|Buck|1958|loc=p.41}}.

