{{Use British (Oxford) English|date=January 2012}} '''ISO/IEC 18014''' ''Information technology — Security techniques — [[Timestamp|Time-stamping]] services'' is an [[international standard]] that specifies time-stamping techniques. It comprises four parts: * ''Part 1: Framework''<ref>[https://www.iso.org/standard/50678.html ISO/IEC 18014-1:2008]</ref> * ''Part 2: Mechanisms producing independent tokens''<ref>[https://www.iso.org/standard/50482.html ISO/IEC 18014-2:2009]</ref> * ''Part 3: Mechanisms producing linked tokens''<ref>[https://www.iso.org/standard/50457.html ISO/IEC 18014-3:2009]</ref> * ''Part 4: Traceability of time sources''<ref>[https://www.iso.org/standard/59934.html ISO/IEC 18014-4:2015]</ref>
== Part 1: Framework == In this first part of ISO/IEC 18014, several things are explained and developed: * The identification of the objectives of a time authority. * The description of a general model on which time stamping services are based. * The definition of [[Timestamp|time stamping]] services. * The definition of the basic protocols of [[Timestamp|time stamping]]. * The specifications of the protocols between the involved entities.
'''Key words''': [[audit]], [[non-repudiation]], [[security]], [[Time stamp|time-stamp]]
== Part 2: Mechanisms producing independent tokens== A [[Timestamp|time-stamping]] service provides evidence that a data item existed before a certain point in time. [[Timestamp|Time-stamp]] services produce time-stamp [[Access token|token]]s, which are data structures containing a verifiable [[Cryptography|cryptographic]] binding between a [[Representation term|data item's representation]] and a time-value. This part of ISO/IEC 18014 defines [[Timestamp|time-stamping]] mechanisms that produce independent [[Access token|token]]s, which can be verified one by one.
== Part 3: Mechanisms producing linked tokens == This part of ISO/IEC 18014: * Describes a general model for [[Timestamp|time-stamping]] services producing linked [[Access token|token]]s. * Describes the basic components used to construct a time-stamping service of this type. * Defines the [[data structure]]s used to interact with a [[Timestamp|time-stamping]] service of this type. * Describes specific instances of such [[Timestamp|time-stamping]] services.
ISO/IEC 18014-3:2009 describes [[Timestamp|time-stamping]] services producing linked [[Access token|token]]s, that is, tokens that are [[Cryptography|cryptographically]] bound to other tokens produced by these time-stamping services. It describes a general model for time-stamping services of this type and the basic components used to construct a time-stamping service of this type, it defines the data structures and protocols used to interact with a time-stamping service of this type, and it describes specific instances of such time-stamping services.
